{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiskInjector"},{"text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" picks up the daemon and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This uses Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume)."}]},{"text":"Usage","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Usage"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"How It Works","anchor":"How-It-Works","type":"heading","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Attaches the guest’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"text":" using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"text":" without mounting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(to discover the device node).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/"},{"text":" that tells","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"text":" to run the script at boot.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"text":"Thread Safety","anchor":"Thread-Safety","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Process"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread."}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Injects a user-data script into a VM’s guest disk as a macOS LaunchDaemon.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Enumeration","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DiskInjector","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"DiskInjector","frag